Let me double-check by looking at what MindmapRequest expects again (I already have this from my earlier read):

From types/index.ts lines 413-429:
```typescript
export interface MindmapRequest {
  title: string;
  nodes: Array<{
    id: string;
    label: string;
    children?: Array<{
      id: string;
      label: string;
      children?: Array<{
        id: string;
        label: string;
      }>;
    }>;
    icon?: string;
    color?: string;
  }>;
}
```

And from tools.ts lines 32-57, the tool definition uses:
```typescript
{
  name: 'create_mindmap',
  ...
  parameters: {
    ...
    properties: {
      topic: {
        type: 'string',
        description: 'Argomento principale della mappa mentale',
      },
      nodes: { ... }
    },
    required: ['topic', 'nodes'],
  }
}
```

So the AI is being told to provide `topic`, but the TypeScript interface expects `title`. This is the exact bug!
